The Psalms Targum: An English Translation (Edward M. Cook)Psalm 3 1.     A psalm of David, when he fled from the presence of Absalom his son.  2.     O Lord, how many are my oppressors, many who arise against me.  3.     Many say to my soul, “There is no redemption for him in God forever.”  4.     But you, O Lord, are a shield over me, my glory and the one who raises my head.  5.     I pray [with] my voice in the presence of the Lord; he will accept[9] my prayer from the mount of his sanctuary forever.  6.     I lay down, and I slept; I awoke, because the Lord sustains me.  7.     I will not be afraid of the strife[10] of people who have gathered against me all around.  8.     Arise, O Lord, redeem me, O my God; for you have struck all my enemies on their cheek, you have broken the teeth of the wicked.  9.     Redemption is from the presence of the Lord; your blessings are to your people forever.
